[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---CONNECTIVITY PACKAGE SPEC---[39m                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m# Connectivity Package Spec[39m                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mDate: 2026-04-11[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Purpose[39m                                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThis document defines the intended scope of `@relay-assistant/connectivity`.[39m    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThe package owns focused internal coordination messages for assistant systems [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mwith multiple active components, specialists, or subsystems.[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mIt exists to make internal communication:[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- faster[39m                                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- smaller[39m                                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- more selective[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- easier to synthesize[39m                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- less chat-like[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Position In The Stack[39m                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mConnectivity sits:[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- above Relay transport and delivery primitives[39m                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- beside `@relay-assistant/coordination`[39m                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- adjacent to `@relay-assistant/routing`[39m                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- below product-specific specialist behavior in Sage, MSD, NightCTO, and future[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m assistants[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Core Thesis[39m                                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mAssistant systems should not treat internal coordination as generic chatter.[39m    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mGeneric chatter causes predictable failures:[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- broad fanout of low-value messages[39m                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- hidden urgency[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- repeated restatement of local reasoning[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- synthesis delays[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- token waste[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- poor interrupt discipline[39m                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mFocused coordination messages solve for a different objective:[39m                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- communicate only what changes downstream action[39m                               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- communicate it to the smallest useful audience[39m                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- make urgency, confidence, and state explicit[39m                                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- suppress messages that do not materially move the system forward[39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- converge on one coherent assistant answer[39m                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Boundary[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### Connectivity owns[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- message classes and signal classes for assistant-internal coordination[39m        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- signal envelopes above transport[39m                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- routing-aware delivery intent such as narrowcast, broadcast, or [39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcoordinator-only[39m                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- communication efficiency policies[39m                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- interruption and escalation semantics[39m                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- convergence semantics such as consensus and conflict handling[39m                 [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### Connectivity does not own[39m                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- raw transport or queue infrastructure[39m                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- provider SDK integration[39m                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- product-specific specialist taxonomies[39m                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- final work assignment graphs[39m                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- cloud-only communication systems[39m                                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## Distinction From Adjacent Packages[39m                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m### vs `@relay-assistant/coordination`[39m                                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mCoordination owns who is doing what.[39m                                            [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mConnectivity owns what minimal signals move between those participants while [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mwork is in pro[39m                                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +1450 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231me the minimum signal classes and semantics needed now[39m                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m5. specify how connectivity can influence routing without owning routing[39m        [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mEnd the document with V1_CONNECTIVITY_SCOPE_READY.[39m                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
